    "section": "Advanced",
    "slides": [
        {
            "id": "s_l6_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "Self Reference 🪞",
            "content": "What if an object wants to talk about its own properties?\n\nIt can use the special keyword `this`."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l6_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l6_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "What does 'this' point to inside a method?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "The global window",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "The object itself",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "`this` refers to the object the method belongs to."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l6_3",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Using 'this' 👉",
            "content": "`this.name` means \"MY name\".",
            "codeSnippet": "let person = {\n  name: 'Sam',\n  introduce() {\n    console.log('Hi, I am ' + this.name);\n  }\n};\n\nperson.introduce(); // Hi, I am Sam",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l6_4",
            "type": "tip",
            "title": "Arrow Functions 🏹",
            "content": "## Careful!\n\nArrow functions do NOT support `this` in the same way.\n\nStick to normal functions for object methods if you need `this`."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l6_5",
